The follow question was asked of these gentlemen during the Boston Fan Fair;<br>
<br>
Scott Hartsman: Technical Director for EverQuest Live, Expansions, and Localizations.<br>
<br>
Ryan Barker: Associate Game Designer for Planes of Power, coordinator for Legends content.<br>
<br>
Paul Carrico: Associate Game Designer for Planes of Power.<br>
<br>
Jeremy Albert: Associate Game Designer for Planes of Power.<br>
<br>
_________________________________________________<br>
<br>
Is Charisma actually taken into account on mesmerizations and charms?<br>
<br>
Yes it is. It varies on a number of spells to its actual usefulness but it does have a use. There are different levels of charisma for different classes. The system does take into account that an Enchanter should have a higher charisma than say a Necromancer. It’s unfair to expect masters of the undead to be entirely charismatic.<br>
<br>
Link;<br>
eq.crgaming.com/viewartic...ticle=4451<br>
<br>
I notice when my cha buff drops my mez's are resisted more.<br>
