<br>
The bulk of the discussion here has been about normal xp grouping.  I have found that Charisma does help with Mezzing and that 150 was (I think) a breakpoint in this.  I have no scientific data on this just annecdotal in my own game.  It doesn't due a lot of good to raise Intelligence above 200, at that point +mana items are of greater value.<br>
<br>
Separately the view of what is required for raiding needs to focus on resist gear, especially given the changes over the past few months.  I work hard to find resist gear that has +intelligence, +mana, or +charisma.  I want to be as useful as possible for raiding and that needs some of all the stats.<br>
<br>
So, the things I look for on gear are Mana, Intelligence, Charisma, and Resists.  I find that the Hitpoints/AC that I can get from gear is of lower importance because I can get better upgrades from my local cleric.<br>
<br>
As a final note, this is from the view of a Human Enchanter and I know there are not too many of those (I have seen High Elf, Erudite, Dark Elf and Gnome in that order) more often than other human enchanters.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 57 Chanter<br>
Vazelle<br>
