<br>
Two different camps each making &quot;gospel&quot; proclamations: Yes it matters, and No it doesn't.<br>
<br>
I have a friend who plays a 65 'chanter on a different server than mine and she tells me that it makes NO difference. She keeps her CHA at 110 for the merchant cutoff. Beyond that, it matters not.<br>
<br>
I have another friend who doesn't play the game much anymore, but he took a 'chanter to level 54 pre-Luclin. In his opinion, CHA is all-important when trying to mez mobs above level 50.<br>
<br>
So who am I supposed to believe? I've had my CHA at 255 and had just as many mezzes resisted as I have leaving it down around 140. I don't use charm much, if at all, so I cannot make judgement there. However, my first friend (the one who thinks it doesn't matter) routinely charms unmezzable mobs as part of her crowd control strategy...with a CHA of 110.<br>
<br>
So, really until I see someone from Verant who writes the code for the game come forth and say for sure one way or the other, I'll just play it safe and keep INT and CHA as high as possible. With the buffs we have available, that's pretty easy to do.<br>
<br>
 <p>Falala
</br>
Level 56 High Elf Enchanter
